@database "Extention.guide"
@width 80
@node main "Extention List Contents"

       @{b} Amiga Guide Extention Lister

       By Robbie Wegner. V1.7@{ub}

    Click here to @{"Search" system "run S:ExtListersearch Sample1.Guide.1 "} for string.

 List of @{"  Documents   " link " .~(info|#?.info) 10000"} WORKBENCH:Documents/

 List of @{"   Pictures   " link " .~(info|#?.info) 10011"} PICTURES:Raytrace

 List of @{" Song Moduals " link " .~(info|#?.info) 10022"} STORAGE:Songs/New/

 INFO-
  This is a sample "Seperate Extention types for each Directory selection"
 guide generated by the ExtLister script.

   It uses the "Find All Extention files" option on. This will find and list
 any extention file in the directory selected. This is useful for directories
 that contain extention files that can all use the same Default tool (and Extra
 button tool if selected).
  The script will allow you to select more extention types for that directory,
 but is pretty pointless since they will all be listed by the first one.
 However! You may want several identical lists but which have different
 Default tools to do different things with the extention files for instance.
 This is generally handled by the Extra Button Tool, but you may want more
 than two Default tools for each file.
   There is also no point in turning the "Directory ALL" list option on for this
 guide, even though you can. The same goes for "THE WORKS!" list, but they are
 available if you want them!
   Notice in the Song modual list that selecting all extention files allows
 you to pick up songmoduals that begin with MOD.#?

  An alternate to using this search method is to use the OR Dos pattern in the
 manual entry for the extention type (at the guides creation). This will search
 for multiple specific file extentions and put them all in one list.
 For example-

 (.doc|.guide|.txt|.readme)
 
 -will only list files with these extentions if there are other extentions in
 the directory that you do not wish to be included in the list.

  The Sorted List switch has been left off. They are all sorted by directory,
 rather than by file.

 NOTE: The search function will not work until the ExtListerSearch file is put
 in the S: directory and AskEnv is put in the C: directory.

  You cannot load the actual files listed, cos they are on my machine :^) 
@endnode
